Elmer L. MOOMAW v. READING COMPANY, Appellant. No. 9115. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Argued June 19, 1946. Decided July 3, 1946. Henry R. Heebner, of Philadelphia, Pa. (Wm. Clarke Mason, of Philadelphia, Pa., of the brief), for appellant. George H. Detweiler, of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellee.

Before BIGGS, McLAUGHLIN, and O’CONNELL, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Consideration of the briefs and the appendix leads us to the conclusion that the court below committed no error. The judgment, 66 F.Supp. 636, is affirmed.
